\cf0 \cb4 ### Expert profile \'97 global promotions (first-session discount & packages)\
\
**Scope:** These are **market-wide** settings (\'93any eligible learner\'94), configured on the **Expert Profile** (or equivalent **Booking / pricing** settings). They are **not** per-learner **special booking** rows (`freelance_work`).\
\
**Registration vs profile:** Onboarding (expert registration / setup wizard) may **collect initial values**, but the **live source of truth** is whatever the Bible names for published expert config (e.g. **`expert_profiles`** + **`expert_availability`** and/or **`expert_packages`**). Edits on the profile **immediately** affect what new learners see (subject to validation and moderation rules).\
\
**First-session discount (FSD):** Expert enables FSD with **rules** (e.g. percent or fixed amount; optional **session-length** constraint if product requires). **Eligibility** is enforced **server-side** (e.g. learner has **not** already had a **qualifying completed/paid session** with this expert \'97 define \'93qualifying\'94 in the Bible). At **checkout**, when FSD applies, write or reserve **`discount_redemptions`** per \'93discount_redemptions\'94 section; **void** if payment fails or booking is cancelled before charge.\
\
**Packages:** Experts define **sellable packages** as **`expert_packages`** rows (one or many). **Purchase** uses the **package checkout** path only (not special-booking accept). On successful payment: **`transactions`** + **`learner_package_credits`**; redemption uses **`package_credit_redemptions`** and atomic credit decrement as in \'93Packages \'97 credits and purchase.\'94\
\
**Learner-facing:** Public **Expert Profile** shows FSD and purchasable packages when enabled and the expert is visible per visibility rules. **Traditional session booking** checkout applies FSD when eligible; **package** CTA opens package purchase flow.\
\
**Implementation alignment:** See **\'93Implementation contract \'97 single source of truth\'94** (B1d) and **Table** fields in B1b.\cf3 \cb1 \
