\cf2 \cb4 Set up email/SMS notifications with an explicit auth boundary:\
\
- Auth boundary:\
  - Use Supabase Auth for user identity.\
  - Do not rely on \'93public\'94 client writes for notification logic.\
  - All outbound email/SMS (and template resolution) runs only on the server (Route Handler / server action / trusted backend), using the Supabase **service role** or equivalent server secret \'97 never from the browser.\
\
- Implementation options (v2 \'97 pick one primary pattern; document which in deployment runbooks):\
  - **Option A \'97 DB trigger + HTTP:** On `INSERT` into `messages`, a database trigger invokes `notify_new_message()` (or equivalent) which calls the app via `pg_net` / `http_post` (or Supabase Edge Function that forwards to the app).\
  - **Option B \'97 DB trigger + Edge Function:** Trigger calls a Supabase Edge Function that sends mail/SMS directly from the function (no intermediate Express requirement).\
  - **Option C \'97 Outbox queue:** Trigger inserts into `notification_outbox`; a worker/cron drains the queue. (Use when you need retries and stricter ordering.)\
\
- DB-triggered events (inbox / new message):\
  - When a new row is inserted into `messages`, the system must notify the **non-sender** participant of the parent `conversations` row.\
  - Webhook / worker payload MUST use **Bible v2 column names**:\
    - `message_id` (PK of `messages`)\
    - `conversation_id` (FK to `conversations`)\
    - `sender_id` (FK to `users.user_id`)\
  - The server resolves recipient by loading `conversations.expert_user_id` and `conversations.learner_user_id` and selecting the user where `sender_id` is the other party.\
  - Do **not** document camelCase JSON (`messageId`, etc.) as canonical; if the wire format uses camelCase, specify an explicit mapping table in the implementation appendix only.\
\
- Canonical HTTP endpoints (notification + cron) \'97 paths are stable whether the app is Express or Next.js Route Handlers; only the host/base URL changes per environment:\
  - `POST /api/notifications/webhook/message` \'97 invoked by DB trigger, Edge Function, or outbox worker. **Body (JSON):** `\{ "message_id", "conversation_id", "sender_id" \}`. **Auth:** require a shared secret (e.g. header `Authorization: Bearer <NOTIFICATION_WEBHOOK_SECRET>` or `X-Webhook-Secret: <\'85>`). Reject unauthenticated calls.\
  - `GET` or `POST /api/notifications/check-booking-reminders` \'97 invoked by an external **cron** (Render/Railway/Vercel Cron, GitHub Actions, etc.). **Auth:** require a cron secret (query param or header, e.g. `CRON_SECRET`). Reject unauthenticated calls.\
  - **Booking reminder selection rule (v2):** query `bookings` using Bible fields `expert_user_id`, `learner_user_id`, `session_date`, `start_time`, and **only** statuses that mean \'93session is still expected to occur\'94 (define explicitly: e.g. `upcoming` and, if used, `payment_status` / confirmation flags per Bible). Do **not** reference legacy v1 values such as `confirmed` unless the Bible explicitly lists them as aliases.\
\
- Cron-based reminders:\
  - Schedule the cron job to call `GET` or `POST /api/notifications/check-booking-reminders` at least every **1\'962 minutes** (or a longer interval if the time window in code is widened accordingly).\
  - Reminder send time is computed from `session_date` + `start_time` in the user\'92s display timezone rules per Bible (typically derived from `users.time_zone` / hometown rules).\
  - Optional: keep a SQL helper (e.g. `check_booking_reminders()` returning candidate rows) **only** as an implementation detail; the **contract** in the Bible is the HTTP cron endpoint + v2 column names.\
\
- Authorization:\
  - For any endpoint that sends notifications or marks notification state:\
    - require server-level authorization (service role / cron secret / webhook secret) as above.\
\
- Templates:\
  - Store notification templates and message rules in the database.\
  - Add an admin UI section with input fields to edit/update templates in DB.\
  - Explicitly define template tokens/variables (subject/body/deep links) and include versioning/auditing via `updated_at` (and optionally `version`).\
\
Template publish rule:\
- Template edits require an admin \'93publish\'94 step.\
- When published, it replaces the stored template in the database and applies to all future auto-sends.\
- Unpublished edits do not affect existing scheduled/future auto-sends until published.\
