#UserType\
To avoid confusion: everyone who registers is considered a user. \
Every user is also a learner, meaning that they are allowed to book experts. \
The term \'93learner\'94 should only be used to define the \'93booker\'94 of experts, all \'93learner\'94 data is stored in the \'93user\'94 table.\
Some users are also Experts. Only users with approved expert profiles can book sessions with learners.\
An expert should be able to \'93Switch to Learning\'94, ie switch from their Expert Profile to their Learning Profile, if they want to book sessions with an expert.\
If an expert is logged in to their expert profile, and attempts to book another expert, show them a prompt that says: \'93You must switch to your learning profile to book other experts. Use the menu at the upper right to switch to learning.\'94\
