\cf2 \cb4 ### Non\uc0\u8209 subscription charges (extensions, freelance, packages, offers)\
\
**Scope:** Any one\uc0\u8209 time or non\u8209 recurring learner charge processed as a Stripe PaymentIntent (or equivalent) **except** subscription plans. Each charge produces a **`transactions`** row (or adjustment row) so learner history, expert payout, and tax reporting stay consistent.\
\
**Charge categories (examples \'97 use `transaction_type` or parallel FKs in schema):**\
- **session_booking** \'97 primary session; `booking_id` required; formulas in **Session pricing & ledger**.\
- **session_extension** \'97 additional 15\uc0\u8209 min blocks after initial booking; `booking_id` required. **Taxable base** = expert rate \'d7 extension blocks (after any extension discount rules). Apply **same** platform % and tax % as session booking. Store extension portion in **`transactions.extensions_amount`** (or a dedicated column) and/or link to a child line; expert **earnings** for that row = extension **booking_amount** (taxable base before platform/tax), unless Bible defines a bundle rule.\
- **freelance_work** \'97 `freelance_id` required; **taxable base** = negotiated **total_price** (or `rate` \'d7 agreed units per `freelance_work` rules). **Platform fee** = 10% \'d7 taxable base; **taxes_fees** = 6% \'d7 (taxable base + platform fee); **total_charge** = sum of those three. **expert_earnings** = taxable base (amount released to expert when work is approved), unless a different split is defined.\
- **package_purchase** \'97 `package_id` / credit grant; **taxable base** = package **total_price** from **`expert_packages`** (after discounts). Same 10% / 6% stack. **expert_earnings** = taxable base (or prorated per Bible when credits are redeemed).\
- **custom_offer** / **prep_review** (if separate from `freelance_work`) \'97 same stack: define **taxable base** from the offer row, then platform 10%, tax 6% on (base + platform), **total_charge**, **expert_earnings** = base unless specified otherwise.\
\
**Universal fee stack (default for all categories above):**\
- Let **B** = **taxable base** (the amount the expert is \'93paid for\'94 before platform and tax \'97 session fee, extension fee, freelance total, package price, etc.).\
- **platform_fee** = 10% \'d7 **B**\
- **subtotal_pre_tax** = **B** + **platform_fee**\
- **taxes_fees** = 6% \'d7 **subtotal_pre_tax**\
- **total_charge** = **B** + **platform_fee** + **taxes_fees**\
- **expert_earnings** = **B** (for standard marketplace sessions, extensions, freelance, and packages unless Bible states an exception).\
\
**UI:** For every charge type, learner sees **Subtotal** = **B** + **platform_fee** and a **Cost totals** breakdown; then taxes; then **Total** \'97 same pattern as session booking.\
\
**`transactions` table (Bible):** Add **`transaction_type`** (enum) and nullable FKs **`freelance_id`**, **`package_id`**, **`booking_id`** (booking_id populated for session + extension charges). Exactly one \'93primary\'94 link should be set per row. **Subscriptions** do not use this row type.\
\
**Implementation:** One shared server function **`computeMarketplaceCharge(\{ taxableBase \})`** returns `\{ platform_fee, taxes_fees, total_charge \}`; category\uc0\u8209 specific code supplies **B** only. Do not duplicate percentage logic per product surface.\
